snippet.textDisplay:
Hello Seth, I'm a financially challenged biker and would like to buy a full suspension that is about my price range. There is one here in the Philippines the Trinx Brave 1.1 that is worth 22,500php or 450usd. If you have the time or anyone else can review it for me? I don't have much experience with better bikes. And I don't like to ask advice from the shop owner becayse maybe the things he say is just for the sale and there are no in depth reviews in the Philippines, and most likely don't use it on rough terrain. I live near a mountain and bike there alot. Buying 2nd hand isn't much of an option also because most people here that sells 2nd hand bikes don't know what depreciation means, and would often sell a 3year old bike that has been used on semi rough terrain for 75% of it original price which is still hard for me. So would pretty love the advice.

P.S been subscribed for 1yr and 2 months now, You're the reason I've been able to do bunny hops now

snippet.textDisplay:
That new line looks awesome, but it's kinda crooked at some parts. In the bird's eye shots, you can see that there are some slight curves where it really should be straight...

I know this is probably because the log had these slight imperfections too, but an easy fix would be to use a bit wider planks just on that part of the log. I feel like that should at least decrease the difficulty a bit. Still, great video! I hope for more builds in the near future :D

Sorry I've got to put to this - Put that Fu**ing chainsaw down.
Buy some proper PPE you've bought a professional saw yet have NO respect for it. I love your Videos Seth I really do. So for the sake of you, your lively hood and the love of riding bikes DO IT. Get an all in 3 helmet, visor and ear defenders Its awesome to see you've at least some chaps & steal boots. I didn't take it seriously at first but seeing so many injuries online it's not worth taking the risk. I've only been using saws for 18months but they are one the most dangerous powertools out there. PS still love the video take care of yourself.
